 2001-12842001-07-160,  ,  FAIT,  , 
PrecisAppointment of PHILIPPE BEAULNE as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Guinea; ANNA BIOLIK as Consul General of Canada at St. Peterburg (Russian Federation); JEAN-PIERRE BOLDUC as High Commissioner for Canada in the Republic of Ghana; DENIS BRIAND as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to Burkina-Faso; ANTHONY BURGER as Consul General of Canada at Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (People's Republic of China); JOSEPH CARON as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the People's Republic of China; DENIS COMEAU as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Korea; KENNETH MURRAY COOK as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Haiti; HECTOR COWAN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Kazakhstan; MICHEL DE SALABERRY as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Arab Republic of Egypt; ADÈLE DION as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Finland; JOHN DONAGHY as High Commissioner for Canada in New Zealand with concurrent accreditation to the Kingdom of Tonga and Kiribati; PAUL DURAND as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada and Permanent Representative of Canada to the Organization of American States; YVES GAGNON as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Kingdom of Morocco; EMILE GAUVREAU as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Côte d'Ivoire with concurrent accreditation to the Republic of Niger; JANET GRAHAM as High Commissioner for Canada in the United Republic of Tanzania, with concurrent accreditation to the Republic of Seychelles, and as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Democratic Republic of Madagascar, and the Islamic Federal Republic of the Comoros; INGRID HALL as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Austria with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador and Permanent Representative to the International Organizations in Vienna; SUSAN HARPER as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Eastern Republic of Uruguay; JEAN-PAUL HUBERT as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Swiss Confederation with concurrent accreditation to the Principality of Liechtenstein; THOMAS MacDONALD as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Argentine Republic with concurrent accreditation to the Republic of Paraguay; SERGE MARCOUX as High Commissioner for Canada in the Co-operative Republic of Guyana; PETER McGOVERN as Consul General of Canada at Milan (Italian Republic); LOUISE OUIMET as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Mali; PATRICK PARISOT as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Chile; EVELYN PUXLEY as Ambassador and Permanent Representative of Canada to the Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe; ANDREW ROBINSON as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to Ukraine; HUGUES ROUSSEAU as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Peru with concurrent accreditation to the Republic of Bolivia; COLIN RUSSEL as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Venezuela; GERALD SKINNER as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Iceland; and OTTFRIED VON FINKENSTEIN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Ecuador.
